6.2 LIMIT OF LIABILITY (b) In the event of any breach or default by Changepoint of any of the provisions of this Agreement, or with respect to any claim arising therefrom or related hereto, except for claims related to Section 5.2 (Unauthorized Disclosure of Confidential Information), or for a breach of Section 6.4(A) (Intellectual Property Indemnity), Changepoint's liability, regardless of the form of action, whether based on contract or tort, including negligence, will in no circumstances surpass:

(i) The amount paid by the Customer for the Licensed Materials as per this Agreement;
(ii) The maintenance service fee paid by the Customer for the service at the heart of the claim, if the claim pertains to a breach or default by Changepoint under Article 7;
(iii) The installation service fee paid by the Customer for the service in question, should the claim concern a breach or default by Changepoint regarding the provisions associated with the Installation Service within this Agreement; or
(iv) In total across all claims arising from or related to this Agreement, the sum paid by the Customer under this contract. The liability limitation set forth above will apply regardless of the number of claims and the nature of damages suffered by the Customer.
